The index of refraction of the water can be calculated using Snell's law, which states that the ratio of the sine of the angle of incidence to the sine of the angle of refraction is equal to the ratio of the indices of refraction of the two media.

In this case, the angle of incidence is 25∘, and the angle of refraction is 90∘ (since the light rays are traveling in the water). The indices of refraction are the index of refraction of the water and the index of refraction of air, which is 1.00.

